# AI Section Component Guidelines

## Content Structure

AI-related components should focus on explaining the relationship between monorepos and AI development workflows.

### Key Content Areas

1. **Context and Understanding**: How monorepos provide better context to AI tools
2. **Development Workflows**: How AI assistants work better with unified codebases
3. **Practical Benefits**: Concrete advantages for developers using AI in monorepos

## Component Layout Patterns

### Two-Column Layout with Content Positioning

```tsx
<div className="mt-16 lg:grid lg:grid-cols-2 lg:items-center lg:gap-8">
  <div className="lg:order-2">{/* Content on the right */}</div>
  <div className="mt-10 lg:order-1 lg:mt-0">
    {/* Complementary content on the left */}
  </div>
</div>
```

### Standard Single Column Layout

```tsx
<div className="mt-16 lg:grid lg:grid-cols-2 lg:items-center lg:gap-8">
  <div>{/* Main content */}</div>
  <div className="mt-10 lg:mt-0">{/* Supporting content/images */}</div>
</div>
```

## Content Sections Structure

When creating feature lists, use the definition list pattern:

```tsx
<dl className="mt-10 space-y-10">
  <div className="relative">
    <dt>
      <div className="absolute flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-md bg-slate-100 text-gray-800 dark:bg-slate-900 dark:text-gray-200">
        <IconName className="h-6 w-6" aria-hidden="true" />
      </div>
      <p className="ml-16 text-lg font-medium leading-6 text-gray-900 dark:text-white">
        Feature Title
      </p>
    </dt>
    <dd className="ml-16 mt-2 text-base text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
      Feature description
    </dd>
  </div>
</dl>
```

